  "created_at": "2025-05-23T14:35:17.000Z",
  "level_num": "custom",
  "user_id": 0,
  "properties": {
    "long_instructions": "# Ethics of AI Collaboration\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #B7E0E5; border-radius: 10px; padding: 15px; margin: 20px auto; max-width: 85%; box-sizing: border-box; word-wrap: break-word; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; margin-top: 12px; line-height: 120%;\">📖 <strong>Ethics</strong> the branch of philosophy that deals with what is morally right and wrong, and how decisions affect people and society.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; margin-top: 12px; line-height: 120%;\">📖 <strong>Copyright</strong> the legal right granted to the creator of an original work to use, distribute, and modify it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; margin-top: 12px; line-height: 120%;\">📖 <strong>Attribution</strong> the act of giving credit to the original creator of a work, especially in the context of using or referencing their material.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 14pt; margin-top: 12px; line-height: 120%;\">📖 <strong>Transparency</strong> the practice of openly disclosing how something works, especially in terms of decision-making, data use, or AI processes.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n#### AI-generated content can blur the line between real and misleading; consequently, here are some ethical and legal challenges it's risen.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-top: 15px;\">\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background: #fff; padding: 15px; text-align: center; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); border: 2px solid #5a2ca0; font-size: 18px\">\r\n\t<p style=\"font-size: 14px\">In 2023, controversy arose when AI-generated books—\tcreated using tools like ChatGPT—were listed on Amazon under fake author names and marketed as legitimate works.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background: #fff; padding: 15px; text-align: center; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); border: 2px solid #5a2ca0; font-size: 18px\">\r\n\t<p style=\"font-size: 14px\">Debates over \"real art\" raged in 2022 after an AI-generated artwork titled \"Théâtre D’opéra Spatial\", created using MidJourney, won first place at the Colorado State Fair’s digital art competition.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background: #fff; padding: 15px; text-align: center; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); border: 2px solid #5a2ca0; font-size: 18px\">\r\n\t<p style=\"font-size: 14px\">In 2023, major music companies filed lawsuits against AI music platforms Suno AI and Udio AI, accusing them of using copyrighted songs without permission. These tools generate new music from user prompts, raising serious questions about ownership, consent, and compensation.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background: #fff; padding: 15px; text-align: center; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 3px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); border: 2px solid #5a2ca0; font-size: 18px\">\r\n\t<p style=\"font-size: 14px\">In 2023, artists and authors sued AI companies, arguing their copyrighted works were scraped and used without permission. They believe this practice is not just illegal—but also unethical—because it harms their ability to earn a living.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #a6e3e8; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px;\">\r\n\r\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-size: 18px; \"><strong>Teacher Tip:</strong> The vocabulary is introduced at the start of the lesson, and then students explore the related ideas in a stations activity. Encourage students to use the vocabulary words throughout the activity and following discussions to help reinforce them.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n## 📝 To Do\r\n#### Choose **one** of the following questions to answer. Write an answer that reflects your personal position. Then, explain your reasoning, including what legal, ethical, or creative values guided your decision.\r\n* #### Who should own AI-generated content - the AI creator, the user, the company, or shared ownership? What happens if AI uses copyrighted material in training?\r\n* #### Should AI-generated art be considered “real art”? Who should get credit—the AI, the programmer, or the person providing the prompt?\r\n* #### Should musicians have control over AI trained on their music? Who should be compensated when AI-generated music is sold?\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display: flex; align-items: left; margin:20px 0px 30px 0px\">\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://forum.code.org/t/teaching-problem-solving-with-ai-pl-reflection-ai-ethics/41004\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/7dbe63a051fbad4ef262d6ab710e2966-image-1731959037460.png\" style=\"width: auto; height: 100px;\"  alt=\"A browser with two text boxes, both including an avatar and lines of text.\"></a>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #007786; border-radius: 20px 20px 20px 20px; color: #000000; width: 80%; margin-left: 5%; margin-right: 5%; padding: 10px 10px 5px 10px;\">\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\"><b>Post to the Code.org Forum</b></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"color: white; line-height: 1.2; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; font-size: 18px\">Share your response and read other educators' ideas on the forum! Click on the icon to the left to direct to our forum post.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; background-color: #F5F7F8; padding: 10px; border-left: 5px solid #8148B2; display: inline-block;\">\r\n    ➡️ This activity is from Lesson 11. You can find more details in the full <a href='https://studio.code.org/s/aif1-2025/lessons/11' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer' style='text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold;'>Lesson Plan</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n",
